At initial referral, a computer tomography angiography (CTA) confirmed a 6,3 x 7,3 cm type III Crawford thoraco-abdominal aneurysm (TAAA), extending from the mid descending thoracic aorta to the aortic-iliac bifurcation (fig 1
a +b). The descending aorta was ectatic and “shaggy” with large amounts of irregular intraluminal thrombus (Fig. 2
). The left kidney was anthropic and renal scintigraphy confirmed that the left kidney only contributed 22% of overall renal function.
